        <!--news-story last pxBuffer --> 
        
        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>The Mechanics of Property Tax Abatement</h1>
          <span class="date">By Matt Eckerle, {if "" != ""},{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} May 13, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1MattEckerle.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/MattEckerle.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>In the last issues of Vision, we’ve talked about Tax Increment Financing (TIF) and property tax abatement as financial tools for your “toolbox” of local incentives to make your community a more desirable location in the eyes of new or growing companies. (If you missed the first two installments, you can <a data-cke-saved-href="http://www.umbaugh.com/latest-news/Property-Tax-Abatement-Another-Economic-Development-Tool-Part-2-in-the-s" href="http://www.umbaugh.com/latest-news/Property-Tax-Abatement-Another-Economic-Development-Tool-Part-2-in-the-s">read them here</a>.)</p>

<p>In basic terms, a property tax abatement is a phasing in of property taxes over a defined period of time for new real property improvements, new buildings and new equipment (personal property).</p>

<p><b>The New “Super Abatements”</b></p>

<p>Senate Enrolled Act 1, passed during the 2014 legislative session, created a new “super abatement” for business personal property that is new to Indiana which becomes effective July 1, 2015. To qualify for this new deduction, the designating body must approve a company’s Statement of Benefits after June 30, 2015. The difference from existing personal property abatement rules is that the personal property tax abatement can be granted for up to 20 years. The process for applying for this super abatement is similar to the existing processes to apply for personal property tax abatement. The designating body (city/town council or county council) may establish an enhanced abatement schedule specifying the percentage amount of the deduction for each year of the abatement term.</p>

<p>If the approved deduction period exceeds 10 years, the designating body must conduct a public hearing to review the taxpayer’s compliance with the approved Statement of Benefits (i.e. did the company meet its targets for jobs, investment and wages) following the 10th year. A penalty may be assessed on the taxpayer by the unit if it is determined the taxpayer has not complied with the Statement of Benefits.</p>

<p>A county or municipality receiving a reimbursement or other penalty due to noncompliance must distribute the received funds on a pro rata basis to each taxing unit in which the property was located.</p>

<p>A community should evaluate the costs and benefits of providing a 20-year super abatement as an incentive. This is a long period of time for a company not to pay property taxes to the community and other taxing units. A super abatement may be justifiable if there are other significant economic benefits to the community from the company’s new investment. Other abatement terms should be considered. Perhaps a 50% abatement (rather than 100%) for 20 years or a traditional 10-year tax abatement or a shorter term would be more appropriate. If tax increment financing (TIF) is part of the incentive mix, some alternative structure may be better. Umbaugh can help you explore alternatives with the company you are encouraging to locate or expand in your community.</p>

<p>In our next article of the series, we’ll explain a strategy for analyzing a potential abatement when a company has both new and existing personal property.</p>

<p>If you have questions about TIF, Tax Abatement or the new Super Abatements, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_jWbRWXZrhK='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_jWbRWXZrhK'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
