        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Cumulative Funds</h1>
          <span class="date">By Paige E. Sansone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} April 29, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1pgregory.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/pgregory.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>Is it time to establish or re-establish the rate on your cumulative fund? The main reasons to do so include: accumulating funds for future capital expenditures, eliminating or reducing the need to borrow (and the interest costs that go with it) and, in some cases, alleviating burdens on operating funds.</p>

<p>Indiana law allows several cumulative funds, however the Cumulative Capital Development Fund (CCD Fund) is the most common and allows the most flexibility. Current law allows the municipal CCD (and the Cumulative Capital Improvement Cigarette Tax Fund) to be used for any legal purpose of a taxing unit, thus potentially improving your ability to pay for operating and capital needs. County CCD Funds are limited to capital improvements and purchases.</p>

<p>Only one cumulative fund is allowed outside the maximum levy limitations. If an additional cumulative fund is established, the Department of Local Government Finance (DLGF) will reduce another controlled fund levy by the new cumulative fund levy.</p>

<p><b>If you do not have any cumulative funds</b>, you may be missing out on an opportunity for additional tax dollars!</p>

<p><b>If you have a CCD Fund</b>, you may have noticed the rate declining over the past few years, possibly related to reassessment and annual trending. There is a process to re-establish the rate back to the maximum. Maximum CCD Fund rates are:</p>

<p><b>Municipalities</b></p>
<ul>
    <li>$.05 - in counties that have adopted CAGIT or COIT</li>
    <li>$.04 – in counties without CAGIT or COIT</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Counties</b></p>
<ul>
    <li>$.0333 – in counties that have adopted CAGIT or COIT</li>
    <li>$.0233 – in counties without CAGIT or COIT</li>
</ul>

<p>The same process is used for establishing or re-establishing a cumulative fund tax rate. The legislative or fiscal body must approve the rate at an advertised public hearing. A Notice of Adoption is published afterward, which starts a period of time for taxpayer remonstrance. When the remonstrance period expires, the proofs of publication, signed ordinance or resolution and a procedure checklist (available from the DLGF) must be forwarded to DLGF no later than <b>August 1</b>.</p>

<p>If you have questions regarding the process or need assistance with establishing a cumulative fund or any other budgetary planning, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_NwgemRsHjS='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_NwgemRsHjS'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
          <div id="tabs">
            <ul>
              <li id="first"><a href="#tabs-1">Give Article Feedback</a> &raquo;</li>
              <li>|</li>
              <li><a href="#tabs-2">E-mail Umbaugh</a> &raquo;</li>
              <li>|</li>
