        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Property Tax Abatement: Another Economic Development Tool</h1>
          <span class="date">By Matt Eckerle, {if "" != ""},{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} April 15, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1MattEckerle.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/MattEckerle.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>In a <a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/latest-news/tif-flexibility-can-benefit-schools-and-other-taxing-units" data-cke-saved-href="http://www.umbaugh.com/latest-news/tif-flexibility-can-benefit-schools-and-other-taxing-units">previous issue of Vision</a>, we talked about Tax Increment Financing (TIF) as one financial tool to help communities compete for economic development projects to grow their tax base and bring jobs to the community. Property tax <b>abatement</b> is another financial tool for your “toolbox” of local incentives to make your community a more desirable location in the eyes of new or growing companies. Recent legislative changes have provided increased flexibility for the application of property tax abatements, most recently with the introduction of the “super” abatements available for new personal property investments.</p>

<p>In basic terms, a property tax abatement is a phasing in of property taxes over a defined period of time for new real property improvements, new buildings and new equipment (personal property).</p>

<p><b>The disadvantages:</b></p>
<ol>
    <li>Unlike TIF, a property tax abatement does not provide up-front capital or fund infrastructure needed to support an economic development project.<br>
</li>
    <li>It delays the benefit of the new assessed value to local governments.</li>
</ol>

<p><b>The advantages:</b></p>
<ol>
    <li>Property tax abatement lowers a company’s operating expenses – which can make your location more desirable as a place for them to start or grow their business.</li>
    <li>Property tax abatement grows assessed value over time, producing benefits for all taxing units.</li>
    <li>Local governments have flexibility in how abatements are structured.</li>
    <li>There are additional benefits of economic development – such as jobs and increased local spending.</li>
</ol>

<p><b>Do you have to choose between TIF and property tax abatement? </b></p>

<p>No. It is possible to use both, but it is important to understand the relationship between the two tools. When TIF and property tax abatement are used in combination with one another, property tax abatement will reduce the amount of TIF revenues available to fund projects.</p>

<p>In future issues, we’ll cover more information about property tax abatements.</p>

<p>If you have questions about TIF, Tax Abatement or the new Super Abatements, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_wbWslakqOe='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_wbWslakqOe'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
