        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>TIF Flexibility Can Benefit Schools and Other Taxing Units</h1>
          <span class="date">By Loren M. Matthes, {if "" != ""},{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} March 03, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1lmatthes.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/lmatthes.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>Tax increment financing (TIF) can have a broad impact that goes beyond the geographic area or businesses it is designed to serve. TIF is one of the few funding methods available to local governments to finance the incentives and infrastructure necessary to compete for economic development. Indiana law allows TIF to be used in a variety of ways to encourage economic development.</p>

<p>TIF does not take away existing revenue. When a TIF district is created, property tax revenue from all or part of the new assessed value in the TIF district is captured for a fixed period of time to pay for incentives or infrastructure capital costs, such as improvements in roads, water systems and sewers. The ultimate purpose of TIF is to increase the tax base (&ldquo;grow the pie&rdquo;) for all local government entities and schools.</p>

<p>The immediate benefits of economic development and TIF include new roads and infrastructure, new jobs and income, increased local income taxes, increased local spending and enhanced &ldquo;quality of place.&rdquo; A number of TIF districts capture only part of the TIF, allowing a portion of the new value to flow to the tax base and all taxing units immediately.</p>

<p>Since the advent of Indiana&rsquo;s property tax caps, many schools and governmental units have experienced shrinking revenue. In fact, $800 million of annual revenue is lost each year to property tax caps throughout the state. With the property tax revenue &ldquo;pie&rdquo; shrinking, building flexibility into TIF agreements can share the TIF benefit without cutting the pie.</p>

<p>Projects funded by TIF must be tied to economic development, but creative TIF agreements can benefit other taxing units as well as all taxpayers in the county&mdash;and even people who just drive through your county.</p>

<p>Let us give you some examples of creatively applying TIF revenues:</p>

<p>In Decatur County, TIF revenue from the Honda plant funds infrastructure for this manufacturing facility, which has brought new jobs and built assessed value. But it has also funded 911 system upgrades, road projects, salt trucks and weather warning systems that serve citizens near the Honda&rsquo;s facility and provide infrastructure to support current and future development.</p>

<p>In Gibson County, TIF revenue from Toyota similarly has brought new jobs and increased assessed value from Toyota&rsquo;s investment and other new businesses that serve Toyota. The nearly $135 million of pass-through assessed value (the uncaptured TIF portion) comprised 17.7% of the school district&rsquo;s net assessed value in 2014. Revenues from the Toyota TIF also to support the construction of a new public meeting space at the county fairgrounds and help expand course offerings at Ivy Tech&rsquo;s Princeton Instructional Center.</p>

<p>In Plainfield, town and school officials have found a number of ways to work together to use a portion of the TIF funds to help schools. TIF is used to pay bonds issued by the school district to fund its bus facility (which is located within a TIF area). The town also issued bonds payable from general property taxes to expand roads around the new high school, and the redevelopment commission releases $100 million of TIF assessed value each year to all taxing units.</p>

<p>TIF revenue can be used for certain educational programs and facilities because it is building a workforce to support economic development. Redevelopment commissions in Marshall County are using TIF revenue for STEM (science, technology, engineering and math) programs. Several communities have used TIF revenues to support local Ivy Tech campuses because of their vital role in preparing a trained workforce. The City of Franklin has partnered with its local school district to use TIF funds to provide Google Chromebooks computers to students.<br />
<br />
Collaboration among governmental units, such as using TIF revenues to directly fund projects or releasing additional TIF area assessed value to other taxing units, is a creative way to address the budget stresses local governments face every day.<br />
<br />
If you have questions about TIF-sharing concepts, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_SoKLnycpHG='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_SoKLnycpHG'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

          <div id="tabs">
            <ul>
              <li id="first"><a href="#tabs-1">Give Article Feedback</a> &raquo;</li>
              <li>|</li>
              <li><a href="#tabs-2">E-mail Umbaugh</a> &raquo;</li>
              <li>|</li>
              <li>
                <FORM>
                  <INPUT TYPE="button" value="Print Article" onClick="window.print()" class="articleBtn">
                </FORM>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <div id="tabs-1" class="tab_content" style="display: none;">
              <h2>Send your feedback:</h2>
              <div class="contact">
                                                <form id="feedback" action="tif-flexibility-can-benefit-schools-and-other-taxing-units" method="post" name="feedback">
                  <div style="float:left; width:318px;">
                    <div class="formblock">
                      <label class="screen-reader-text">Is this item worthy of implementation?</label>
                      <input type="radio" name="feedback1" value="Yes">
                      Yes
                      <input type="radio" name="feedback1" value="No">
                      No
                      <input type="radio" name="feedback1" value="Maybe">
                      Maybe <br />
                    </div>
                    <div class="formblock">
                      <label class="screen-reader-text">Is this item worth sharing with other associates?</label>
                      <input type="radio" name="feedback2" value="Yes">
                      Yes
                      <input type="radio" name="feedback2" value="No">
                      No
                      <input type="radio" name="feedback2" value="Maybe">
                      Maybe <br />
                    </div>
                    <div class="formblock">
                      <label class="screen-reader-text">Did this item present value to you and your business?</label>
