        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Will Annexation Laws Change?</h1>
          <span class="date">By Deen C. Rogers, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} February 10, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1drodgers.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/drodgers.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>The Interim Study Committee on Government finalized its recommendations in October for how Indiana should deal with annexations. These recommendations have found their way into bills during the 2015 legislative session.</p>

<p>Indiana is among a minority of states that permit municipalities to initiate an annexation. However, according to the results of a survey conducted by the Indiana Advisory Commission on Intergovernmental Relations, most annexations after 2009 have been voluntary annexations. Voluntary annexations are initiated by a majority of the landowners in the annexed area.</p>

<p>Concerns presented in testimony before the committee included resolving annexation disputes, loss of revenue to counties and other taxing entities, protecting the rights of landowners, the cost of remonstrating, extending municipal services to the annexed areas, and compensation to electric utilities for lost service areas.</p>

<p>These points summarize the Committee’s recommendations:</p>

<p>• Require approval from the owners of 51% of parcels before annexation may proceed.<br>
• Remonstrance against an annexation shall prevail if the owners of 50% plus one of the parcels object.<br>
• County officials should have a voice in annexations.<br>
• Consent of the county executive should be required for extension of the two mile fringe when annexation occurs.<br>
• Tax exempt property should be exempted from the parcel count for remonstrance purposes.<br>
• The fiscal plan must include a spreadsheet containing detailed parcel data.<br>
• The fiscal plan must include a four-year projection of services and tax impacts; the Department of Local Government Finance (DLGF) should review the plan for completeness.<br>
• The fiscal plan may not be amended after a remonstrance is filed, unless the remonstrators consent to it.<br>
• Fiscal plan requirements should model the government modernization code.<br>
• The municipality should be required to publicly inform and engage the community in discussions at least six months before drafting the fiscal plan or adopting an annexation ordinance.<br>
• Annexation cannot be certified until entry of a final judgment.<br>
• The exemption for agricultural land should be based on how the land is used, not its zoning designation.<br>
• Prohibit bypassing of low value or high service need areas when surrounding properties are annexed.<br>
• Municipalities should be required to accept petitions for voluntary annexation when 7/8 of the annexation boundary is contiguous.<br>
• An appropriate committee should study local option income tax reform, and an appropriate committee should study rules to prevent battles between municipalities over contested areas.<br>
• The standing committees for utility matters should address the impact of annexation on electric utility service areas during the 2015 session.</p>

<p>Recommendations do not always result in successful bills, but they are a good indicator of what may be discussed during the legislative session.</p>

<p>We will continue to actively monitor any annexation rule changes and will provide additional information when known.</p>

<p>If you have questions or need help with an annexation, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_FiLBZvWPIJ='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_FiLBZvWPIJ'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
