        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Doug Baldessari Becomes IWEA Officer</h1>
          <span class="date">By Umbaugh Announcements, {if "" != ""},{/if} {if "" != ""},{/if} February 04, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1dbaldessari.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/dbaldessari.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>We congratulate Umbaugh Partner Doug Baldessari, CPA for being elected secretary-treasurer of the Indiana Water Environment Association (IWEA) for 2015.</p>

<p>Doug leads our utility practice group firmwide and has been active in IWEA for several years, serving as the chair of the Utility Management Committee and working with IWEA and the Indiana Section of the American Water Works Association to help organize their Joint Utility Management Conference.</p>

<p>IWEA also presented Doug with its prestigious Tumble Bug Award in November for meritorious service to the association.</p>

<p>IWEA is dedicated to preserving and protecting Indiana’s waterways through educating its members and Indiana citizens about the importance of our water environment, and we’re proud to have Doug serving in a leadership role on its Board.</p>

<p>We also want to congratulate and recognize Umbaugh Senior Associate, Jessica Eckerle, CPA for being selected as co-chair of the IWEA Young Professionals Committee for 2015.</p>

<p>Umbaugh is committed to active involvement in organizations that support our clients and improve the communities they serve!</p>
