        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Upcoming Deadlines</h1>
          <span class="date">By Paige E. Sansone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} January 08, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1pgregory.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/pgregory.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>As the New Year begins, it is time to focus on wrapping up the previous year. At the close of December, all records must be posted and reconciled with bank statements as promptly as possible. Utilities and other departments maintaining separate records must also be reconciled. Below are upcoming deadlines prescribed by the State Board of Accounts for the first few months of the year. Please note that this is not a comprehensive list; you should check the State Board of Accounts Accounting and Compliance Guidelines Manuals for more information at <a href="http://www.in.gov/sboa/#">http://www.in.gov/sboa/#</a>.</p>

<p>January 31 is the last day to furnish each employee with a Form W-2 showing compensation paid during the preceding year, federal tax withheld and Social Security tax withheld.</p>

<p>January 31* is the last day to file the Form 100R (Report of Names, Addresses, Duties and Compensation of Public Employees) with the State Board of Accounts. This form must be filed electronically through Gateway.</p>

<p>February 17 is the last day for the meeting of the Township Board to consider and approve, in whole or in part, the Annual Financial Report of the Township Trustee.</p>

<p>February 27 is the last day for the Township Trustee to file a copy of the Annual Financial Report and accompanying vouchers in the County Auditor’s Office.</p>

<p>February 28 is the last day to file withholding statements W-2 and WH-2 together with Yearly Reconcilement of Employer’s Quarterly Tax Returns W-3 and WH-3 with District Director of Internal Revenue and Indiana Department of Revenue, respectively.</p>

<p>March 1* is the last day to file the Annual Financial Report on Gateway.</p>

<p>March 1 is the last day to publish the Annual Financial Report for all local units except Townships.</p>

<p>March 1* is the last day to complete an annual review and verify accuracy of debt information in Gateway Debt Management.</p>

<p>March 1 is the last day to prepare a list of checks for cancellation that have been outstanding and unpaid for two years.</p>

<p>March 1 is the last day to file Video Franchise Fee Report with IURC.</p>

<p>March 2 is the last day to file Other Post Employment Benefits (OPEB) through Gateway. This applies to all political subdivisions including those that do not offer OPEB.</p>

<p>March 15 is the last day for the Redevelopment Commission to file with the unit’s executive a report setting out activities during the preceding calendar year. The report must be submitted as a PDF through Gateway.</p>

<p>March 17 is the last day for the Township Trustee to publish the abstract stating that a complete and detailed annual report and the accompanying vouchers have been filed with the County Auditor and that the Chairman of the Township Legislative Body has a copy of the report available for inspection by any taxpayer of the Township.</p>

<p>April 1 is the last day to file Water Utility Resource Report with IURC. This applies to all municipal utilities including those not regulated by the IURC.</p>

<p>April 30 is the last day to file the Annual Utility Report with the IURC. This applies to regulated municipal utilities only.</p>

<p>* Failure to file one or more of the following reports may result in denial of your budget by the DLGF: 100R, Annual Financial Report, and Debt Management Report.</p>

<p><i>If you have any questions about the above deadlines, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_OJklgnukpl='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_OJklgnukpl'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</i></p>
