        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Form 100R due January 31, 2015</h1>
          <span class="date">By Paige E. Sansone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} January 08, 2015</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1pgregory.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/pgregory.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>Each year local government entities are required to submit a Certified Report of Names, Addresses, Duties and Compensation of Public Employees also known as a Form 100R. All people employed in 2014 must be reported including Elected Officials, Board Members, and part-time, temporary and seasonal employees. If a W2 was issued, that person should be reported on the 100R.</p>

<p>It is important to note that an employee&rsquo;s total compensation must be reported on the 100R. The State Board of Accounts uses IRS Publication 15 guidelines to define compensation.</p>

<p>The 100R is filed electronically through Gateway and is due no later than January 31, 2015. Please remember to download, sign and mail the Attestation Statement to the State Board of Accounts within five days of the electronic Gateway submission. If the 100R is modified, a new attestation statement must be signed and mailed.</p>

<p>Be aware that in addition to employee compensation, other information is required such as whether a unit offers a health plan, a pension, and other benefits to full- and part- time employees. A unit must also indicate whether it has implemented a nepotism policy and contracting policy.</p>

<p>New for 2014 &ndash; a PDF of the nepotism and contracting policies must be uploaded to Gateway. Failure to file the 100R may be cause for the DLGF to deny a taxing unit&rsquo;s budget. If your 2013 100R has not been filed, please contact <span data-eeEncEmail_iNGSvsJAbv='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 118',' 111',' 103',' 46',' 110',' 105',' 46',' 97',' 111',' 98',' 115',' 64',' 115',' 116',' 114',' 111',' 112',' 101',' 114',' 108',' 97',' 117',' 110',' 110',' 97','>','\"',' 118',' 111',' 103',' 46',' 110',' 105',' 46',' 97',' 111',' 98',' 115',' 64',' 115',' 116',' 114',' 111',' 112',' 101',' 114',' 108',' 97',' 117',' 110',' 110',' 97',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_iNGSvsJAbv'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script> and request to have the 2013 100R unlocked in order to complete and submit.</p>

<p><i>If you have any questions about the 100R please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_iWVpeQIIEB='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_iWVpeQIIEB'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</i></p>

