        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Proactive Financial Management for Utilities</h1>
          <span class="date">By Eric Walsh, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Manager" != ""}Manager,{/if} December 09, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1walsh.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/walsh.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>We all know how important it is to maintain a budget and keep council members and department heads up to speed about appropriation spending throughout the year for tax-supported funds. Does your city, town or district take this same approach with utilities?</p>

<p>Umbaugh has created a service line called Financial Management Reporting (FMR) to meet the specific needs of municipal utilities. Currently, more than 60 utilities throughout Indiana use FMR to accomplish strong financial management objectives, including:</p>

<p>&bull; <ins>Rate Management</ins> &ndash; This proactive approach to rate initiatives keeps decision makers in-the-know about potential rate adjustments well before the need arises, which gives you sufficient time for planning and public education.<br />
&bull; <ins>Accounting Support</ins> - How much would it cost to have a CPA on your utility staff? FMR provides utility accounting support throughout the year as questions arise.<br />
&bull; <ins>Annual Utility Budgeting</ins> - Although not required by the State as it is for tax- supported funds, a utility budget is the cornerstone of sound financial decisions.<br />
&bull; <ins>Capital Planning</ins> - During the FMR process we work closely with utility management to develop a multi-year capital plan and provide recommendations on its affordability.<br />
&bull; <ins>Debt Management</ins> &ndash; FMR provides regular review and recommendations regarding historical and potential debt, including analyzing refunding opportunities and the current bond market.<br />
&bull; <ins>Large Customer Analysis</ins> - It is not uncommon for a handful of customers to generate a large portion of a utility&rsquo;s revenue. FMR analyzes billings and collections for your largest customers in a way that provides meaningful information for decision makers.<br />
&bull; <ins>Comparative Financial Information</ins> - FMR provides key historical and forecasted financial data side-by-side to allow trend analysis and benchmarking.<br />
&bull; <ins>Narrative Summary</ins> &ndash; Because some people are numbers people and some aren&rsquo;t, FMR provides information in a narrative summary as well as data. A narrative summary is often beneficial to council members who don&rsquo;t see the day-to-day utility numbers and are looking for a summary overview of the utility&rsquo;s financial health.<br />
&bull; <ins>Tailored Specifically for You</ins> - Financial information doesn&rsquo;t come in a one-size-fits-all package. We tailor reports to meet the specific needs of your utility personnel, council, clerk-treasurer and other decision makers.<br />
&bull; <ins>Periodic Reporting</ins> - Annual, semiannual and quarterly reporting packages tailored to your specific needs are all available, creating positive habits for regularly reviewing the utility&rsquo;s financial health.</p>

<p><b>Is FMR right for you?</b></p>

<p>FMR is used by utility personnel, councils, clerk-treasurers and other appointed officials for short-term budgetary control, cash management, cost accounting, long-term capital planning and rate management.</p>

<p>These reports, and the services included with them, serve as an effective tool for training, communication and to increase the overall understanding of the complexities and unique needs of municipal utilities. How well you have communicated at the local level is often considered by debt-rating agencies when you seek financing. In addition, the reports and services satisfy technical requirements for preparing financial statements in accordance with Indiana State Board of Accounts standards.</p>

<p>Finally, our clients value the independent analysis that Umbaugh FMR provides to validate management actions and decisions.</p>

<p>The start of a new year is a good time to apply FMR to your utility management.</p>

<p>If you have questions or would like to know more about FMR, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_notzIBLdaQ='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_notzIBLdaQ'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>

