        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>How to Reallocate Circuit Breaker Credits</h1>
          <span class="date">By Paige E. Sansone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} August 08, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1pgregory.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/pgregory.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          
	  <p>Due to Indiana’s implementation of “protected taxes,” a law passed in 2013 authorized reallocating circuit breaker credits beginning in 2014. Protected taxes are levies for debt service and include debt that is both exempt and non-exempt from the circuit breaker credits. Circuit breaker credits that should have been applied to debt service funds will instead be applied to the unprotected (non-debt-service) funds. Political subdivisions (except schools that receive a waiver) have the ability, within certain limitations, to transfer tax revenue among unprotected funds after receiving the revenues from the County as a way to reallocate circuit breaker credits. Schools can apply for a waiver from the state for 2014 through 2016 if the circuit breaker loss exceeds 10% of transportation levies. School corporations granted the waiver from protected taxes are not eligible to complete the reallocation process but can allocate the circuit breaker credits proportionately among all property tax supported funds.</p>

<p>The DLGF has provided a Reallocation of Circuit Breaker Credits worksheet to each taxing unit that can be used to request a reallocation of circuit breaker credits. The first numerical column on the worksheet (Initial Circuit Breaker Amount) shows the allocation amount determined by the DLGF, taking into consideration the requirement of protected taxes. The next numerical column shows what DLGF has determined to be the minimum amount of circuit breaker credits that must be applied to each fund. The last column (Unit Reallocation of Circuit Breaker Amount) may be used by a taxing unit to reallocate circuit breaker credits.</p>

<p>Debt service, circuit-breaker-exempt funds, and funds without levies have automatically been assigned a minimum amount of circuit breaker that must be applied and therefore, no changes can be made to those funds.</p>

<p>Circuit breaker credits for all other funds may be reallocated with two limitations:<br>
1. The credits may not be less than the amount shown in the Minimum Amount of Circuit Breaker Required column; and<br>
2. Total circuit breaker credits before and after reallocation must be the same.</p>

<p>Taxing units that wish to reallocate circuit breaker credits are encouraged to have their fiscal body take official action indicating its intent to reallocate. The president of the fiscal body may sign the DLGF reallocation worksheet to signify official action. After the worksheet is signed, submit it to the DLGF for review and approval.</p>

<p>The county will distribute property tax according to the DLGF’s Initial Circuit Breaker Amount and will not take into consideration any approved reallocations. It is the taxing unit’s responsibility to properly transfer its property tax revenue among funds to match the reallocation amounts the fiscal body approved.</p>

<p>The DLGF encouraged submission of the allocation worksheets by July 15, 2014, but since that date has passed the DLGF is requesting submission as soon as possible.</p>

<p>If you have questions or need help determining reallocation amounts, please contact us a <span data-eeEncEmail_aSpAZJducA='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_aSpAZJducA'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
